      }
    }
    // .....
  }
}
{% endcode_block %}

Embark will now no longer deploy that contract, in the dashboard you should see:

![Console](/assets/images/token_factory_2/console_2.png)

## Conclusion

In [part 1](/news/2018/09/27/how-to-create-a-token-factory-with-embark-part-1/) we deployed and interacted with single Token. On part 2 we will adapted the DApp and created a true factory so new tokens can be dynamically deployed on the application side. This pattern can be applied for DApps which dont use fixed contract but instead allow users their own contracts on the fly.

